f=Engineering/axiom/operational/commands/axiom-commands.md · p=Routing reference axiom: which phrase invokes which skill, overlapping "performance" vocabulary resolves. · h2:Trigger Table=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · h2:Trigger Table=\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Trigger Table=\| dsa-design-records \| "which data structure," "what algorithm," "why this structure," "record this choice" \| `/axiom-dsr` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| complexity-analysis \| "what's the complexity," "will it scale," "is this O(n²)," "Big-O" \| `/axiom-complexity` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| performance-profiling \| "optimize," "why slow," "is this faster," "profile it," "benchmark" \| `/axiom-profile` \| · h2:Trigger Table=\| algorithm-review \| "review this algorithm," "is this correct," "will this scale" (a diff) \| `/axiom-review` \| · h3:"will scale slow?" predict measure=Analytical question about growth **complexity-analysis** (predict)., Empirical question about current speed **performance-profiling** (measure)., They disagree measurement wins; analysis gets re-examined. · h3:"optimize" always measure first=optimization before profile (performance-profiling). "Make faster" without measured bottleneck refused premature. · h3:"review" vs "design"=new choice dsa-design-records., Someone else's diff algorithm-review. · h3:Load-bearing only=DSA records deep analysis load-bearing choices/hot paths `list` `set`. Don't gold-plate cold code. · f=clear match it's about growth, complexity-analysis; about current speed, profiling; about choice, record. Ambiguous ask. Requests optimize without measured bottleneck route profiling first.